Brazilian High Education General Perspective

Expedito Pinto de Paula Junior

8/10/2020

1.Context

The INEP is brazilian institute for education reasearch in Ministry of Education. Some of the competences of INEP are:

  • Subsidize the public authorities in the monitoring and evaluation of the National Education System.
  • Support policy planning to guarantee the right to quality education for each and every one.
  • Propose and define performance parameters, criteria and mechanisms for the evaluation of education systems at all levels and modalities, as well as for the skills certification processes, in conjunction with the education systems of the states, the Federal District and the municipalities.
  • Others

Every year, INEP perform the National Student Performance Exam (ENADE) in order to evaluates the performance of graduates of undergraduate courses in relation to the syllabus provided in the curricular guidelines of the courses, the development of competences and skills necessary to deepen general and professional training, and the level of updating of students in relation to the Brazilian and world reality.

In INEP Web site are available several datasets denomitate The INEP Microdata, these datasets constitute the lowest level of disaggregation of data collected by surveys, evaluations and examinations.

Each edition (year) of the evaluation has focus in different fields of study. More information about it are available in Exame Nacional de Desempenho de Estudantes

2.Synopsis

Using Exploratory Data Analysis method this analysis explore the The INEP Microdata and address some basic questions about the National Student Performance Exam in the last 10 years:

    1. Is higher education in Brazil improving?
    1. Where Brazil have the best number in education? per rea and also per courses.
    1. In relation to the past generation, is higher education improving?
    1. In what modalities of higher education is Brazil improving?
    1. Which courses in which college are best rated?

QE_I13 Question: What is your fathers education level?
QE_I14 Question: What is your fathers education level?

3.3 Extracting data subset and converge variable names

Based in the difference from the two previous tables, we are going two extract the varialbles from the datasets and convert to variable names from 2010 to 2018. Other important point to analysis is create a unique dataset for all years.

3.3.1 Identifying possible filters parameters.

According with the dataset documentation, some parameters must be considering in filter in order to have cleaning data for analysis. These parameters are related to the presence of the student in the Tests. For this analysis is considering presence in all tests. These paramenters are showed bellow:

Table 4: Filters from 2008 to 2018
Variables Description Value
tp_pres/TP_PRES Presence Type 555 = Present
tp_pr_ger/TP_PR_GER Presence Type In Test 555 = OK
tp_pr_ob_fg/TP_PR_OB_FG Presence Type In Test for General Formation in Objective part 555 = OK
tp_pr_di_fg/TP_PR_DI_FG Presence Type In Test for General Formation in Discursive part 555 = OK
tp_pr_ob_ce/TP_PR_OB_CE Presence Type In Test for Specific Component in Objective part 555 = OK

3.3.2 Subset data

In this section the data will be filtered according to table 3 for all datasets. Then, only the variables of interest are selected by normalizing the variable names and including all datasets in a single dataset.
